<subSubSection id="C3720CC7FFD3FFD5FF797517FCA3F688" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD75F4CFFD3FFD5FF797517FC23F624" blockId="20.[151,1436,1354,2036]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF797517FEFFF525" bold="true" box="[151,275,1354,1379]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Medium size (
<quantity id="4C90F2A9FFD3FFD5FE247516FDA7F525" box="[458,587,1355,1379]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="17.0">17–22 mm</quantity>
) and body robust (
<figureCitation id="135343C9FFD3FFD5FCDC7517FC67F525" box="[818,907,1354,1379]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–61" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[193,1417,285,1973]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[150,1436,255,1973]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 57–61. Griffinigryllacris n. gen. 57–59. G. reunionis n. comb. Female habitus, frons and male terminalia. 60–61. Frons of G. mauritiana n. comb. and G. adelungi n. comb." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944859/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Head globose and prominent, ocelli poorly developed, space between antennal cavities as wide as scape (
<figureCitation id="135343C9FFD3FFD5FC927533FBD2F5C1" box="[892,1086,1390,1415]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–61" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[193,1417,285,1973]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[150,1436,255,1973]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 57–61. Griffinigryllacris n. gen. 57–59. G. reunionis n. comb. Female habitus, frons and male terminalia. 60–61. Frons of G. mauritiana n. comb. and G. adelungi n. comb." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944859/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 58, 60, 61</figureCitation>
); fore coxa with a small and unarticulated spine, legs moderately short and robust, with four pairs of movable ventral spines on fore and middle tibiae; wings well developed, ovoid, without surpassing the apex of abdomen. Abdomen without traces of femoroabdominal apparatus; 10 
<superScript id="7C1DF204FFD3FFD5FE457587FE5BF5AE" attach="left" box="[427,439,1498,1512]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite of the male little modified and with two small hooks; subgenital plate short and rectangular, wider than long, with simple styles and without modification on the notch (
<figureCitation id="135343C9FFD3FFD5FB0F765CFADAF65C" box="[1249,1334,1537,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–61" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[193,1417,285,1973]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[150,1436,255,1973]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 57–61. Griffinigryllacris n. gen. 57–59. G. reunionis n. comb. Female habitus, frons and male terminalia. 60–61. Frons of G. mauritiana n. comb. and G. adelungi n. comb." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944859/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Female abdomen with unspecialized tergites; female genital plate simple and triangular; ovipositor as long as abdomen and curved from the middle section, rather thin and with sharp apex (
<figureCitation id="135343C9FFD3FFD5FC807614FC2EF624" box="[878,962,1609,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–61" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[193,1417,285,1973]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[150,1436,255,1973]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 57–61. Griffinigryllacris n. gen. 57–59. G. reunionis n. comb. Female habitus, frons and male terminalia. 60–61. Frons of G. mauritiana n. comb. and G. adelungi n. comb." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2944859/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD75F4CFFD3FFD5FF297630FCA3F688" blockId="20.[151,1436,1354,2036]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF297630FE44F6C0" bold="true" box="[199,424,1645,1670]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Included species:</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54D3E1EEFFD3FFD5FE2D7633FE16F6C0" box="[451,506,1646,1670]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FD677630FB76F6C0" authority="(Karny, 1932)" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Karny" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[649,1178,1645,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Griffinigryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reunionis" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FD677630FC23F6C3" box="[649,975,1645,1670]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Griffinigryllacris reunionis</emphasis>
(Karny, 1932)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22F3E25FFD3FFD5FB587630FADCF6C0" box="[1206,1328,1645,1670]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FB587630FADCF6C0" bold="true" box="[1206,1328,1645,1670]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">n. comb.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(before 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FF7976CCFEB0F6EC" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[151,348,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Niphetogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF7976CCFEB0F6EC" box="[151,348,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Niphetogryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and two additional species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FD5676CFFBE9F6EC" authority="(Griffini, 1911 c)" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Griffini" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[696,1029,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Griffinigryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adelungi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FD5676CFFCD1F6EC" box="[696,829,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">G. adelungi</emphasis>
(Griffini, 1911c)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22F3E25FFD3FFD5FBFE76CCFB96F6EC" box="[1040,1146,1681,1706]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FBFE76CCFB96F6EC" bold="true" box="[1040,1146,1681,1706]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">n. comb.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FB6276CFFF08F688" authority="(Griffini, 1909 c)" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Griffini" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Griffinigryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritiana" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FB6276CFFAC0F6EF" box="[1164,1324,1682,1705]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">G. mauritiana</emphasis>
(Griffini, 1909c)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22F3E25FFD3FFD5FF0276E8FEBDF688" box="[236,337,1717,1742]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF0276E8FEBDF688" bold="true" box="[236,337,1717,1742]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">n. comb.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(these two species before 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FD9476E8FCD3F688" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[634,831,1717,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Niphetogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FD9476E8FCD3F688" box="[634,831,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Niphetogryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3720CC7FFD3FFD5FF297684FF18F7B2" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD75F4CFFD3FFD5FF297684FBE6F750" blockId="20.[151,1436,1354,2036]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF297684FEBDF6B4" bold="true" box="[199,337,1753,1778]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology:</emphasis>
Dedicated to the memory of Achille Griffini as a recognition to his great contributions to raspy crickets, plus typical termination— 
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FDCC76A0FD63F750" box="[546,655,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">gryllacris</emphasis>
common to genera of this family.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD75F4CFFD3FFD5FF29777CFF18F7B2" blockId="20.[151,1436,1354,2036]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF29777CFE88F77C" bold="true" box="[199,356,1825,1850]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Comparison:</emphasis>
The new genus differs from the African genera and others relative taxa from its prominent head, 9 
<superScript id="7C1DF204FFD3FFD5FF4B7718FF5DF715" attach="left" box="[165,177,1861,1875]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">th</superScript>
abdominal tergite unmodified, 10 
<superScript id="7C1DF204FFD3FFD5FDDE7718FDD0F715" attach="left" box="[560,572,1861,1875]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">th</superScript>
with hooks little developed, notch of the subgenital plate straight in contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FF5B7732FE8DF7CE" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[181,353,1903,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Stictogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FF5B7732FE8DF7CE" box="[181,353,1903,1928]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Stictogryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species who have the 9 
<superScript id="7C1DF204FFD3FFD5FD9A7731FD6CF73C" attach="left" box="[628,640,1900,1914]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">th</superScript>
tergite with denticulations, 10 
<superScript id="7C1DF204FFD3FFD5FC327731FC04F73C" attach="left" box="[988,1000,1900,1914]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">th</superScript>
tergite with hooks well developedand some species with the notch bilobated. The females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FCDC77CEFC1FF7EA" authority="Cadena-Castañeda, 2019" authorityName="Cadena-Castañeda" authorityYear="2019" box="[818,1011,1939,1964]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Griffinigryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FCDC77CEFC1FF7EA" box="[818,1011,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Griffinigryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FB2677CEFA70F7EA" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[1224,1436,1939,1964]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Barombogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FB2677CEFA70F7EA" box="[1224,1436,1939,1964]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Barombogryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females for its longer wings and straight or little curved ovipositor (the ovipositor in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6824CFFFD3FFD5FBA577EAFAF3F796" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1937" box="[1099,1311,1975,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Barombogryllacris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD3FFD5FBA577EAFAF3F796" box="[1099,1311,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Barombogryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well upcurved).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3720CC7FFD2FFD4FF2970CAFE8CF093" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD75F4CFFD2FFD4FF2970CAFE8CF093" blockId="21.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B91C835EFFD2FFD4FF2970CAFE8EF0F6" bold="true" box="[199,354,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F37F1FDCFFD2FFD4FE8370CAFE18F0F6" box="[365,500,151,176]" name="Madagascar" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and adjacent islands (
<collectingCountry id="F37F1FDCFFD2FFD4FD1570CAFCB0F0F6" box="[763,860,151,176]" name="Réunion" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Reunion</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F37F1FDCFFD2FFD4FC7470CAFBE8F0F6" box="[922,1028,151,176]" name="Mauritius" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mauricio</collectingCountry>
, maybe others unknown species in neighbor islands).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
